  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the grill to high</p><p>Add <strong>half </strong>your <strong>aubergine[s]<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span></strong>(you'll use the rest later!) to a <strong>tin</strong> <strong>foil</strong>-lined baking tray and pierce a few times with a knife, then put the tray under the grill for 20-25 min or until blackened all over and fork-tender</p><p>Once done, remove the tray from the oven and carefully (it will be hot!) scoop the flesh out of the <strong>blackened aubergine</strong> into a bowl and season generously with <strong>salt</strong> – this is your <strong>smoky aubergine</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1878.-step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1878.-step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1878.-step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1878.-step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1878.-step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, boil a kettle</p><p>Peel and slice your <strong>red onion[s]</strong> finely</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your<strong> garlic </strong>and your<strong> ginger</strong></p><p>Peel and dice the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>aubergine[s]</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1878.-step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1878.-step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1878.-step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1878.-step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1878.-step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) over a medium-high heat with 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tbsp] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[4</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">tbsp]</span> <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>sliced onion </strong>with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 8-10 min or until starting to soften</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped garlic</strong>,<strong> chopped ginger </strong>and <strong>diced aubergine</strong> then continue to cook for 3-4 min</p><p>Tip: If your pan starts to look dry, add a little more oil!</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1878.-step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1878.-step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1878.-step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1878.-step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1878.-step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once fragrant, add your<strong> ground coriander</strong>, <strong>cayenne pepper </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!), <strong>half </strong>of your<strong> ground cumin</strong> (you'll use the rest later), <strong>tomato paste</strong> and your <strong>vegetable stock mix</strong> with 250ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[325ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[400ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Reduce the heat to medium and cook, covered, for 8-10 min or until the chopped aubergine is cooked through</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1878.-step-4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1878.-step-4-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1878.-step-4-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1878.-step-4-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1878.-step-4-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Dice your <strong>cucumber</strong> finely and add to a bowl</p><p>Chop your <strong>coriander</strong> roughly, including stalks</p><p>Gently mash the <strong>smoky aubergine</strong> with a spoon</p><p>Once the chopped aubergine is cooked through, stir the <strong>smoky mashed aubergine</strong> and <strong>chopped coriander </strong>through the curry – this is your <strong>Gujarati-style aubergine curry</strong></p><p>Remove from the heat and set aside until serving</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1878.-step-5-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1878.-step-5-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1878.-step-5-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1878.-step-5-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1878.-step-5-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add your <strong>natural yoghurt</strong> and <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>ground cumin</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong>, <strong>pepper</strong> and 1/2 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3/4 tsp] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[1 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar</strong> to the bowl with the<strong> </strong>diced cucumber and give everything a good mix up – this is your <strong>cumin &</strong> <strong>cucumber raita</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1878.-step-6-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1878.-step-6-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1878.-step-6-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1878.-step-6-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1878.-step-6-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your<strong> naan[s]</strong> to a <strong>toaster </strong>for 1-2 min or until warmed through</p><p>Once hot, spread with<strong> butter</strong> and sprinkle with your<strong> nigella seeds</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Mini-naans-in-toaster-1687784343710-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Mini-naans-in-toaster-1687784343710-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Mini-naans-in-toaster-1687784343710-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Mini-naans-in-toaster-1687784343710-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Mini-naans-in-toaster-1687784343710-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the<strong> Gujarati-style aubergine curry</strong> with the <strong>buttered naan</strong> and the<strong> cumin & cucumber raita</strong> to the side</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
